cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
1) cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks and their semantic representation. 
2) cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses a hybrid approach that combines logic-based and distributional semantics through probabilistic logic inference in Markov Logic Networks (MLNs). 
3) cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses machine learning techniques to learn resource-specific weights. 
4) cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper discusses knowledge base construction and inference, which are important in information retrieval tasks. 
5) cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the efficiency of solving inference problems.
